body:
#### PR description:

Updating `SeedingHitSet`: 
- filtering out `nullptr` directly in the constructors dropping `setSize()`;
- adding `std::initializer_list` to allow braced constructors, to have a cleaner doublet, triplet and quadruplet hit constructors;
- relying on `std::size` for the size (with the correction of single-hit set);
- adding tests in `SeedingHitSet_t.cpp`;
- fix bugs in https://github.com/cms-sw/cmssw/issues/36808 & https://github.com/cms-sw/cmssw/issues/36804 

#### PR validation:

1. The tests run. 
2. Tested wfs `1030.0` and `1040.0`with `CMSSW_12_3_ASAN_X_2022-01-26-2300` (that was highlighting the failures) + this PR and it's running. 

FYI: @makortel, @dan131riley, @Dr15Jones
